\f2\b\fs36 Navigating in Copyholders\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf3 <!$Scr_H::1><$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f3\i\b Note:
\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  be sure to go through the section covering Copyholders in \'93Referring to More Documents\'94 before reading this section.\
You can use this same button to navigate documents using {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://3331E0D0-AA13-4653-B607-A1CE10DE1096"}}{\fldrslt Copyholders}}. Try this:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Holding down Option on the keyboard, drag one of the documents in the corkboard or outliner and drop it onto the header bar above the corkboard or outliner. A Copyholder split will open within the other editor.\
{\listtext	2.	}Now click on the \'93Selection Affects Other Editor\'94 button again so that it changes colour, taking on the system accent colour. Then click it a second time. Now that a Copyholder is open, it will remain coloured on this second click, but the icon will change to show the arrow pointing 
\f4\i into
\f0\i0  the box. This indicates that selection will now be opened in the Copyholder rather than in the other editor.\
{\listtext	3.	}Now try selecting documents in the corkboard or outliner\'97see how they get opened in the Copyholder?\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Hopefully you will see how useful this could be. For instance, here\'92s a setup I use quite regularly:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Binder open on left.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Editor split vertically.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Right editor in outliner mode with its Copyholder open at the bottom\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\'93Selection Affects\'94 button set to affect the Copyholder.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Right editor {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://AF621794-7D82-4A10-A93C-092DDCDFFBF4"}}{\fldrslt Locked in Place}} (so that any clicks in the binder only affect the left editor).\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 With this arrangement, I can use the binder to navigate the editor on the left, and the outliner to navigate the Copyholder below it, arranging and editing my manuscript on the left while navigating through and referring to research and notes on the right.\
